  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-02-24",
    "date": "2021-04-02T19:13:30Z",
    "text": "Infrastructure Expansion Act of 2021\n\nThis bill precludes absolute liability in any action against a property owner or contractor for projects that are federally owned or operated or are receiving federal financial assistance for infrastructure and transportation development for any injury associated with an elevation- or gravity-related risk occurring on those projects. In any such claim, a state shall apply a liability standard that considers the comparative negligence of the injured person, when such negligence is a proximate cause of an injury."
  },
